            <title>[LOG4J2-2553] TLS syslog appender: doc suggests to use &lt;TLSSyslog&gt; to configure appender</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-2553</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/manual/appenders.html#SSL&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Docs&lt;/a&gt;&#160;suggest &amp;lt;TLSSyslog&amp;gt; for adding an appender. When I try that I&apos;m getting:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2019-02-25 13:18:13,573 main ERROR Error processing element TLSSyslog (&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Appenders: null&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;): CLASS_NOT_FOUND&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When substituting to &amp;lt;Syslog&amp;gt; - no error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
